    "order": 1,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "The expectation (mean) E[f_{i}'] of the intermediate values f_{i}' is:"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b002",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 2,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "latex": "\\begin{aligned}\n\\mathbb{E}[f_{i}^{\\prime}] &=\\quad\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\beta_{i}+\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\Omega_{ij}h_{j}\\right] \\\\\n&=\\quad\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\beta_{i}\\right]+\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\Omega_{ij}h_{j}\\right] \\\\\n&=\\quad\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\beta_{i}\\right]+\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\Omega_{ij}\\right]\\mathbb{E}\\left[h_{j}\\right] \\\\\n&=\\quad0+\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}0\\cdot\\mathbb{E}\\left[h_{j}\\right]=0,\n\\end{aligned} \\qquad (7.29)"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b003",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 3,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "where $D\\_{h}$ is the dimensionality of the input layer $\\mathbf{h}$. We have used the rules for manipulating expectations, and we have assumed that the distributions over the hidden units $h\\_{j}$ and the network weights $\\Omega\\_{ij}$ are independent between the second and third lines."
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b004",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 4,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "Appendix C.2.1"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b005",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 5,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "Using this result, we see that the variance $\\sigma\\_{f}^{2}$, of the pre-activations $f\\_{i}^{\\prime}$ is:"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b006",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 6,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "latex": "\\begin{aligned}\n\\sigma_{f_{i}}^{2} &=\\mathbb{E}[f_{i}^{\\prime2}]-\\mathbb{E}[f_{i}^{^{\\prime}2}] \\\\\n&=\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\left(\\beta_{i}+\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\Omega_{ij}h_{j}\\right)^{2}\\right]-0 \\\\\n&=\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\left(\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\Omega_{ij}h_{j}\\right)^{2}\\right] \\\\\n&=\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\Omega_{ij}^{2}\\right]\\mathbb{E}\\left[h_{j}^{2}\\right] \\\\\n&=\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\sigma_{\\Omega}^{2}\\mathbb{E}\\left[h_{j}^{2}\\right]=\\sigma_{\\Omega}^{2}\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\mathbb{E}\\left[h_{j}^{2}\\right],\n\\end{aligned} \\qquad (7.30)"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b007",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 7,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "where we have used the variance identity $\\sigma^{2} = \\mathbb{E}[(\\mathbf{z}-\\mathbb{E}[\\mathbf{z}])^{2}] = \\mathbb{E}[\\mathbf{z}^{2}] - \\mathbb{E}[z]^{2}$. We have assumed once more that the distributions of the weights $\\Omega\\_{ij}$ and the hidden units $h\\_j$ are independent between lines three and four."
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b008",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 8,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "Assuming that the distribution of pre-activations $f\\_{j}$ at the previous layer is symmetric about zero, half of these pre-activations will be clipped by the ReLU function, and the second moment $\\mathbb{E}[h\\_{j}^{2}]$ will be half the variance $\\sigma\\_{f}^{2}$ of $f\\_{j}$ (see problem 7.14):"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b009",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 9,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "Appendix C.2.3"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b010",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 10,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "latex": "\\sigma_{f_{i}^{^{\\prime}}}^{2}=\\sigma_{\\Omega}^{^{2}}\\sum_{j=1}^{D_{h}}\\frac{\\sigma_{f}^{^{2}}}{2}=\\frac{1}{2}D_{h}\\sigma_{\\Omega}^{^{2}}\\sigma_{f}^{^{2}}. \\qquad (7.31)"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0109-b011",
    "page_key": 109,
    "order": 11,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "Variance identity"
  }
